                <p class="dictentry-term">Libido</p>
                <p class="dictentry-src"><img src="images/book.gif" alt="" /> Hinshelwood (1991). A
                    Dictionary of Kleinian Thought</p>
                <p class="dictentry-dictalso"><img src="images/arrow_bw.gif" alt="" />
                    <span class="peppopup glosstip" data-width="800" data-type="sticky"
                        data-docid="zbk.069.0001i.yn0006585309640" data-draggable="true"
                        data-direction="southwest">INSTINCTS</span></p>
                <p class="body">Freud's original intention was to develop a quasi-physics of the
                    mind. The details of the theory of the <span class="peppopup glosstip"
                        data-width="800" data-type="sticky"
                        data-docid="zbk.069.0001l.yp0006482592450" data-draggable="true"
                        data-direction="southwest">libido</span> that he developed and the continual
                    modifications to it in his writings and in those of psychoanalytic theorists who
                    came after him is one of the more <span class="peppopup glosstip"
                        data-width="800" data-type="sticky"
                        data-docid="zbk.069.0001c.yn0011849881830" data-draggable="true"
                        data-direction="southwest">complex</span> stories in the <span
                        class="peppopup glosstip" data-width="800" data-type="sticky"
                        data-docid="zbk.069.0001d.yp0008047204240" data-draggable="true"
                        data-direction="southwest">development</span> of <span
                        class="peppopup glosstip" data-width="800" data-type="sticky"
                        data-docid="zbk.069.0001p.yn0004507089640" data-draggable="true"
                        data-direction="southwest">psychoanalysis</span>
                    <span class="peppopup bibtip" data-type="velcro"
                        data-element="zbk.066.0337a.b003" data-maxwidth="300"
                        data-direction="southeast">(Laplanche and Pontalis, 1973)</span>.</p>
                <div class="seemore">
                    <a class="seemore" href="#/Document/zbk.069.0001l#yp0006482592450"
                        >...excerpted...click to open full glossary entry...</a>
                </div>
                <div class="dictentry-bib">
                    <div class="bib" id="zbk.066.0337a.b001">
                        <p class="bib_bib">Abraham, Karl (1924) ‘A short study of the development of
                            the libido’, in Karl Abraham (1927), <i>Selected Papers on
                                Psycho-Analysis</i>, Hogarth, pp. 418-501.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="bib" id="zbk.066.0337a.b002">
                        <p class="bib_bib">Freud, Sigmund (1905) Three Essays on Sexuality.
                                <i>Standard Edition</i> 7, pp. 125-245. <a class="bibx"
